      • RfcQuery

        public RfcQuery(String functionName)
         throws IllegalArgumentException
        Constructs a remote function call query for which the result will be committed.
        Parameters:
        functionName - The name of the function to be called.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the given function is a BAPI, i.e., its name starts with the prefix "BAPI".

      • RfcQuery

        public RfcQuery(String functionName,
        boolean commit)
         throws IllegalArgumentException
        Constructs a remote function call query.
        Parameters:
        functionName - The name of the function to be called.
        commit - Decides whether to commit the result of the function call.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the given function is a BAPI, i.e., its name starts with the prefix "BAPI".
